Java House is a well-established cafe in the Historic Dupont Circle neighborhood. Situated on the warm side of Q St NW, Java House’s large patio offers power outlets along the railing, as well as umbrellas and an extendable awning for shade during warmer days.  Java House is a great place to study, grab weekend (or any day) breakfast & lunch, or extend your work-from-home office for a few hours.
Nice outdoor seating with outlets if you need to do some work on the computer.  Great location :). Recommend the oatmeal and the bagel sandwiches!

After recently leaving the Affordable Housing Rally, I saw Java House and wandered in for some octane  (coffee).  Decided I was hungry and ordered the Avacado BLT .... it is THE BEST one I've ever tasted!  The bacon was not fatty and it was perfectly well done - crispy but not brittle, with a hint of chewy-ness. Multi grain bread is  perfect texture and flavor compliment and avocado was 100% ripe with no brown marks.  Truly memorable.  Coffee con leché was great, too!

Java house is a pretty chill place to grab a cup of coffee and a quick bite to eat. I work from there occasionally during the week since it's close by and their coffee is good. Their food is alright, nothing amazing, but it's decent (a little overpriced though). The service is usually pretty good. It can be difficult to find a plug for your laptop, but generally it's not crowded so it's doable. It has a nice, large, partially covered outdoor patio to sit at when the weather is nice.

The shop is on a great corner in DC and out of 50+ coffee shops, has the best Chai lattes. The salads are generous and wonderful as well, fresh and made right on the spot. I go out of my way to come here consistently and friends are starting to come as well. Definitely must stop in!

This review is on a sliding scale - I believe in ranking places according to what they aspire to be... Java House is an unpretentious coffee shop. The coffee is good, though nothing spectacular. They do have a really nice patio area to soak up some sun while eating your breakfast. On that note, I've found the breakfast sandwiches to be delicious. Try eggs and whatever on a croissant. The servers are reliably fantastic.
